1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,000
https://slama.dev/comeback/

2
00:00:00,150 --> 00:00:08,380
In honor of the visit of Pope Benedict XVI to the Czech Republic, we are replacing the originally planned sinful dance with the suffering of Christ.

3
00:00:08,380 --> 00:00:09,400
Enjoy the show.

4
00:00:10,820 --> 00:00:11,540
Ivo!

5
00:00:12,850 --> 00:00:13,650
Tragedy.

6
00:00:14,050 --> 00:00:15,000
Did they raise the price of cocoa?

7
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:16,280
Don't make light of it.

8
00:00:16,280 --> 00:00:18,850
The building manager called a residents' meeting.

9
00:00:19,250 --> 00:00:20,480
Oh no, is there already an agenda?

10
00:00:20,480 --> 00:00:20,660
Yeah.

11
00:00:21,950 --> 00:00:22,750
First.

12
00:00:23,050 --> 00:00:28,150
Installation of a gate in the basement to prevent hooligans from greasing the stairs with soap.

13
00:00:29,750 --> 00:00:30,450
Second.

14
00:00:30,750 --> 00:00:37,010
Installation of safety barriers to prevent unauthorized sliding of hooligans down the banister.

15
00:00:38,650 --> 00:00:46,330
Third, purchase of chains for the trash cans, so hooligans can't keep moving them in front of the building manager's door.

16
00:00:47,150 --> 00:00:51,250
Fourth, the problem of rat infestation in the building manager's basement.

17
00:00:51,950 --> 00:00:53,050
You know what this means?

18
00:00:53,350 --> 00:00:54,750
34 points, Ozzak.

19
00:00:57,890 --> 00:01:00,190
Did you know that rats love cracklings?

20
00:01:34,250 --> 00:01:35,550
Ozzak is pulling pranks.

21
00:01:36,460 --> 00:01:38,880
The building manager is going to take away our basement, I can feel it in my bones.

22
00:01:39,020 --> 00:01:39,500
She won't.

23
00:01:39,700 --> 00:01:41,020
She already took it from us once.

24
00:01:41,100 --> 00:01:42,140
But she gave it back.

25
00:01:42,160 --> 00:01:43,060
We have it on probation.

26
00:01:44,750 --> 00:01:46,050
Jesus, where will we put the cranberries?

27
00:01:46,950 --> 00:01:49,220
How about we finally throw them out after ten years?

28
00:01:49,450 --> 00:01:52,050
Come on, Ivuska, you know I'm saving them for your wedding.

29
00:01:52,150 --> 00:01:55,150
There's no wedding without a cranberry cake.

30
00:01:55,900 --> 00:01:56,940
I hope I'm a lesbian.

31
00:01:57,160 --> 00:01:57,520
What?

32
00:01:58,450 --> 00:01:59,180
That it's great.

33
00:01:59,180 --> 00:01:59,600
Yeah.

34
00:02:00,450 --> 00:02:01,770
What's gotten into Ozzak?

35
00:02:01,830 --> 00:02:02,730
Why is he acting up?

36
00:02:03,180 --> 00:02:04,400
He's just happy, you know.

37
00:02:04,480 --> 00:02:06,480
He finally found a good pub, so he's happy.

38
00:02:06,660 --> 00:02:07,640
Happy, happy.

39
00:02:07,780 --> 00:02:10,340
But why does everyone around have to be miserable because of his pranks?

40
00:02:13,130 --> 00:02:14,210
Lebrajka, come here, come here.

41
00:02:14,290 --> 00:02:15,050
We need to talk.

42
00:02:16,050 --> 00:02:18,550
Fine, but don't drag it out, I'm heading to the pub.

43
00:02:18,660 --> 00:02:19,960
And what about the first three points?

44
00:02:20,080 --> 00:02:21,320
Well, Satan isn't around the corner.

45
00:02:22,250 --> 00:02:24,770
Can't you pick a pub that's actually in Prague?

46
00:02:24,770 --> 00:02:25,950
But Satan is in Prague.

47
00:02:26,950 --> 00:02:29,350
Haje is technically East Prague, but I don't go there much.

48
00:02:30,350 --> 00:02:32,050
So you'll get home again only tomorrow?

49
00:02:32,350 --> 00:02:33,460
Today I'm getting a ride.

50
00:02:33,650 --> 00:02:34,650
Ziza will drive me.

51
00:02:34,850 --> 00:02:36,330
Ziza has a car?

52
00:02:36,350 --> 00:02:37,450
Sure, a company vehicle.

53
00:02:37,550 --> 00:02:39,770
We just have to make a stop at two septic tanks on the way.

54
00:02:40,150 --> 00:02:41,250
Is that some kind of pub too?

55
00:02:41,450 --> 00:02:43,150
No, she's got a sewage truck.

56
00:02:43,250 --> 00:02:48,570
Look, bro, I was gonna wait in front of the building, but the valve is tight, so it can't sit too long anywhere.

57
00:02:48,570 --> 00:02:49,270
So get going.

58
00:02:51,150 --> 00:02:52,650
Did you get rid of that rat?

59
00:02:52,750 --> 00:02:54,350
Sure, exactly as you said.

60
00:02:54,450 --> 00:02:56,440
Anywhere, just not in the building manager's basement.

61
00:02:56,440 --> 00:02:56,740
Great.

62
00:02:57,340 --> 00:02:58,620
In Vojtickova's basement.

63
00:03:00,220 --> 00:03:01,820
She always goes down there at three to get her rice.

64
00:03:02,300 --> 00:03:03,700
Are you out of your mind?

65
00:03:04,010 --> 00:03:06,370
Mrs. Vojtickova is in cahoots with the building manager.

66
00:03:06,950 --> 00:03:08,950
But even more shrill than the building manager.

67
00:03:10,450 --> 00:03:13,050
See, you could set your watch by her.

68
00:03:14,050 --> 00:03:22,740
Ozzak, please, do you realize that because of your Canadian pranks we could end up in serious trouble? Watch out for Vojtickova.

69
00:03:23,150 --> 00:03:25,350
It's fine with Vojtickova.

70
00:03:26,050 --> 00:03:27,960
I didn't want to say it, but she's hitting on me.

71
00:03:27,960 --> 00:03:28,480
What?

72
00:03:29,750 --> 00:03:31,050
But she's seventy.

73
00:03:31,650 --> 00:03:33,350
Old wood burns the best.

74
00:03:34,230 --> 00:03:34,750
Uncle.

75
00:03:35,250 --> 00:03:36,750
Aren't you confusing her with someone?

76
00:03:37,040 --> 00:03:39,220
Vojtickova is the old lady who calls you a Satanist.

77
00:03:39,400 --> 00:03:41,300
That's what I'm saying, I drive her crazy.

78
00:03:41,950 --> 00:03:43,950
Every time she sees me, she grabs her chest.

79
00:03:43,980 --> 00:03:44,420
What?

80
00:03:44,820 --> 00:03:45,440
I mean...

81
00:03:49,640 --> 00:03:50,080
Jesus.

82
00:03:50,080 --> 00:03:52,550
But she doesn't stand a chance with me, she listens to funk.

83
00:03:52,700 --> 00:03:53,140
Funk?

84
00:03:53,140 --> 00:03:55,250
Yeah, she keeps writing to me about trumpets.

85
00:03:55,950 --> 00:03:58,050
Bro, do you happen to have one of those letters here?

86
00:03:59,450 --> 00:04:04,950
Yeah, but Ivuska shouldn't read it.

87
00:04:05,850 --> 00:04:07,150
The old hag has no shame.

88
00:04:08,750 --> 00:04:10,850
Devil's spawn.

89
00:04:12,950 --> 00:04:13,950
She knows how to get to me.

90
00:04:15,250 --> 00:04:17,750
Living under the same roof with you is hell.

91
00:04:19,050 --> 00:04:25,150
Whenever I see you, I pray that the time for God's judgment has finally come.

92
00:04:26,250 --> 00:04:28,250
If it weren't for the funk, Sheldon.

93
00:04:29,150 --> 00:04:37,750
Then the sinners shall be scorched by the fires of hell, but the righteous shall hear the trumpets of angels.

94
00:04:39,850 --> 00:04:40,650
That'll be Zizak.

95
00:04:40,650 --> 00:04:41,290
Tomas?

96
00:04:58,950 --> 00:05:01,950
Sorry, Marcelka, I had to go back to the building for galoshes.

97
00:05:03,750 --> 00:05:04,550
Why?

98
00:05:04,850 --> 00:05:08,750
Ziza was waiting for Ozzak a bit too long.

99
00:05:09,540 --> 00:05:10,120
Ugh!

100
00:05:11,450 --> 00:05:14,050
Now I'm not surprised the whole east side didn't smell a thing.

101
00:05:14,250 --> 00:05:16,310
But on the radio they said it's supposed to rain tonight.

102
00:05:16,310 --> 00:05:17,010
If only.

103
00:05:20,960 --> 00:05:21,540
Ugh!

104
00:05:25,950 --> 00:05:28,640
I always fall for it.

105
00:05:29,150 --> 00:05:30,580
Ozzak won't get me.

106
00:05:30,850 --> 00:05:31,880
I'm careful now.

107
00:05:32,150 --> 00:05:36,140
After that neoprene on the toilet seat, I'll never sit down for his tricks again.

108
00:05:36,140 --> 00:05:38,180
The register and the accounts are in the cash box.

109
00:05:41,340 --> 00:05:42,160
Marcelka, wait!

110
00:05:43,250 --> 00:05:44,970
I'm rushing to Zoran.

111
00:05:44,970 --> 00:05:47,550
He's getting baptized and forgot his towel.

112
00:05:48,370 --> 00:05:49,050
Zoran?

113
00:05:49,750 --> 00:05:51,950
Well, otherwise the Pope wouldn't receive him.

114
00:05:52,910 --> 00:05:54,590
The Pope is supposed to receive Zoran?

115
00:05:54,770 --> 00:05:56,470
He's giving him a private audience.

116
00:05:56,750 --> 00:05:58,950
And you didn't say anything?

117
00:05:59,210 --> 00:06:01,050
Well, I didn't want to jinx it.

118
00:06:01,150 --> 00:06:03,330
Zoran has been trying for a really long time.

119
00:06:03,410 --> 00:06:05,150
It's an exceptional honor.

120
00:06:05,210 --> 00:06:07,930
Even the mayor couldn't manage it at all.

121
00:06:08,350 --> 00:06:10,850
And Zoran is, you know...

122
00:06:11,750 --> 00:06:12,370
A believer?

123
00:06:12,750 --> 00:06:14,950
He will be, once I bring him that towel.

124
00:06:16,250 --> 00:06:20,550
Don't worry, he's only doing it so his herbal liqueur sells better in Sibenik.

125
00:06:21,050 --> 00:06:22,850
Wait, I don't understand at all.

126
00:06:23,550 --> 00:06:29,050
Zoran gets his photo taken with the Pope, puts it on the bottle, and Benedictinka will sell like hotcakes.

127
00:06:30,250 --> 00:06:31,350
Benedictinka?

128
00:06:31,620 --> 00:06:32,760
New name.

129
00:06:32,780 --> 00:06:36,000
It used to be called Sluze Franje Tudman and before that Tito's Bitter.

130
00:06:36,440 --> 00:06:40,860
Zoran says the Pope sells better today than sex and the Olympics combined.

131
00:06:41,450 --> 00:06:43,280
Maybe in Croatia, but here...

132
00:06:44,050 --> 00:06:45,950
Well, you'd be surprised.

133
00:06:46,650 --> 00:06:48,750
Check out the charts.

134
00:06:52,650 --> 00:06:56,650
All the major Czech artists already figured it out.

135
00:06:57,120 --> 00:06:57,540
What?

136
00:06:58,350 --> 00:07:00,850
Number one, Maxim Turbulenc?

137
00:07:01,550 --> 00:07:03,750
I've Got Jesus in My Belly?

138
00:07:04,750 --> 00:07:05,760
And look further down.

139
00:07:05,760 --> 00:07:06,320
Kabat.

140
00:07:07,050 --> 00:07:08,150
Yeah, Kabat.

141
00:07:08,650 --> 00:07:10,160
God Rode a Goat.

142
00:07:10,160 --> 00:07:12,000
And in third place, the Nedveds.

143
00:07:12,060 --> 00:07:12,880
Amen Means Amen.

144
00:07:14,050 --> 00:07:16,580
And then all the way to tenth place, nothing but religious stuff.

145
00:07:16,580 --> 00:07:18,180
People are buying it like crazy.

146
00:07:18,650 --> 00:07:21,050
So why didn't you just order some right away?

147
00:07:21,750 --> 00:07:25,050
Unfortunately, I can't open the supplier list.

148
00:07:25,550 --> 00:07:26,250
How come?

149
00:07:27,350 --> 00:07:29,650
Ozzak sprinkled sneezing powder on it.

150
00:07:32,350 --> 00:07:33,050
Jesus, the towel.

151
00:07:33,250 --> 00:07:39,450
Marcelka, I promise I'll put a stop to his stupid pranks.

152
00:07:52,920 --> 00:07:59,080
In a surprising move, the mayor urged Praguers to turn to God and announced he would be baptized immediately.

153
00:07:59,200 --> 00:08:03,300
He dismissed speculation that he plans to run in the South Moravian region as blasphemy.

154
00:08:05,060 --> 00:08:06,760
Ivo, drop everything, meeting.

155
00:08:11,150 --> 00:08:13,650
The building manager has the list of residents.

156
00:08:14,850 --> 00:08:16,150
But I outsmarted her.

157
00:08:17,550 --> 00:08:18,750
I went around the doorbells.

158
00:08:19,050 --> 00:08:20,950
Wow, that's really clever.

159
00:08:21,450 --> 00:08:22,550
Why did you take such a risk?

160
00:08:23,550 --> 00:08:29,650
Ivo, if there's going to be a vote about our basement, we need to secure support across the building.

161
00:08:30,050 --> 00:08:32,050
So, which one is Pajerova?

162
00:08:32,350 --> 00:08:34,370
Wait, you don't know everyone in our building?

163
00:08:34,750 --> 00:08:38,050
No, I only really know Simona and the people who come to the shop to complain.

164
00:08:38,110 --> 00:08:39,130
So you know everyone.

165
00:08:39,530 --> 00:08:41,170
And did you get into it with Pajerova?

166
00:08:41,990 --> 00:08:42,390
Me?

167
00:08:42,390 --> 00:08:44,450
Come on, I never argue.

168
00:08:44,850 --> 00:08:47,430
Until someone tells you off for putting glass in the plastic bin.

169
00:08:47,550 --> 00:08:49,250
Yeah, that's still a thing.

170
00:08:49,850 --> 00:08:53,250
Okay, look at it, is there anyone on our side, anyone who kind of likes us?

171
00:08:53,750 --> 00:08:54,450
Roubal.

172
00:08:54,750 --> 00:08:55,810
Great, I'll go see him.

173
00:08:56,050 --> 00:08:58,450
That won't help, he mostly likes me and Sasa.

174
00:09:00,680 --> 00:09:01,080
Next.

175
00:09:02,150 --> 00:09:04,350
Podrouzek, he likes Lexa.

176
00:09:04,550 --> 00:09:05,750
Well, you know.

177
00:09:06,750 --> 00:09:09,250
But who knows if he hasn't gone off on a Scout hike again.

178
00:09:10,350 --> 00:09:11,450
This is hopeless.

179
00:09:12,250 --> 00:09:14,150
If only Simona could be there.

180
00:09:14,450 --> 00:09:15,430
But she's not allowed.

181
00:09:15,430 --> 00:09:15,830
No.

182
00:09:16,350 --> 00:09:19,490
The building manager banned her for two years for unauthorized termination of a meeting.

183
00:09:19,750 --> 00:09:21,150
How unauthorized?

184
00:09:21,450 --> 00:09:24,650
When things were at their worst, she blew the fuses and screamed "watch out, a monitor lizard!"

185
00:09:25,550 --> 00:09:27,620
Since then she has to vote by mail.

186
00:09:27,620 --> 00:09:43,480
That door handle.

187
00:09:44,040 --> 00:09:45,960
I'm going to lose my mind.

188
00:09:45,960 --> 00:09:47,760
Yeah, his Canadian pranks are driving me nuts too.

189
00:09:48,150 --> 00:09:52,150
Last night I dreamed he woke me up and tried that trick with the telescope and the soot on me.

190
00:09:54,550 --> 00:09:58,550
Ivuska, when you go to the bathroom, don't look in the mirror.

191
00:09:59,950 --> 00:10:00,850
I already did, yeah?

192
00:10:01,850 --> 00:10:02,830
Where did this come from?

193
00:10:02,830 --> 00:10:03,770
It was under the door.

194
00:10:05,950 --> 00:10:06,750
Oh my God.

195
00:10:08,750 --> 00:10:12,850
Last night, hooligans stole a bench from the courtyard and the spare ficus from the landing.

196
00:10:13,050 --> 00:10:16,850
The hooligans and those who harbor them face exemplary punishment.

197
00:10:17,450 --> 00:10:18,550
This is like under Heydrich.

198
00:10:19,550 --> 00:10:21,270
Why does she want to take our basement?

199
00:10:21,270 --> 00:10:22,610
She's old and bitter.

200
00:10:24,850 --> 00:10:25,790
I mean Ozzak. It couldn't have been him.

201
00:10:26,150 --> 00:10:27,800
What would he do with a bench and a ficus?

202
00:10:27,800 --> 00:10:29,080
Christ, how would I know?

203
00:10:29,080 --> 00:10:33,700
Same thing he did with the geranium pots, the brooms, and the lids from Hajek's vacuum cleaner.

204
00:10:33,700 --> 00:10:34,140
Candles?

205
00:10:34,950 --> 00:10:37,450
Or the slide, whatever.

206
00:10:37,950 --> 00:10:38,850
What are you doing?

207
00:10:39,060 --> 00:10:40,520
I need to sweeten my life.

208
00:10:40,680 --> 00:10:41,200
That's salt.

209
00:10:41,440 --> 00:10:42,760
Ivo, please, wake up.

210
00:10:43,360 --> 00:10:45,660
Glue on the door handles, tied shoelaces, a volleyball.

211
00:10:46,080 --> 00:10:47,680
He definitely swapped the sugar and salt.

212
00:10:47,820 --> 00:10:48,360
He did.

213
00:10:48,380 --> 00:10:49,080
Well, there you go.

214
00:10:49,200 --> 00:10:49,980
I already swapped them back.

215
00:11:12,060 --> 00:11:12,500
Hi.

216
00:11:12,500 --> 00:11:13,480
Hey, why so early?

217
00:11:13,480 --> 00:11:17,350
Could I have breakfast at your place? Mom took away the table and I don't like eating on the floor.

218
00:11:17,800 --> 00:11:18,240
Sure.

219
00:11:20,140 --> 00:11:20,940
Good morning.

220
00:11:21,180 --> 00:11:21,660
Hi.

221
00:11:22,750 --> 00:11:23,650
Where's Lexa?

222
00:11:24,150 --> 00:11:25,250
He's in the bathtub.

223
00:11:28,550 --> 00:11:31,420
Sasa, where did your mom take the table?

224
00:11:31,750 --> 00:11:34,350
Probably where she put the couch and the carpet, to the resting room.

225
00:11:35,550 --> 00:11:36,950
The resting room?

226
00:11:37,650 --> 00:11:41,150
Mm, Mom says things also need to rest when they've served for a long time.

227
00:11:42,750 --> 00:11:43,750
That's sad.

228
00:11:44,010 --> 00:11:44,490
Why?

229
00:11:44,950 --> 00:11:46,850
Sasa, they'll come back good as new.

230
00:11:47,950 --> 00:11:49,950
So, Sasa, how is your mom actually doing?

231
00:11:50,060 --> 00:11:52,560
Since she lost her job, she's completely stopped going out.

232
00:11:52,700 --> 00:11:55,640
Well, she didn't go anywhere for a long time because she can't stand people feeling sorry for her.

233
00:11:56,450 --> 00:12:01,020
But now that the sisters are going through Croatia, climbing into the tunnel every night, she's in a much better mood.

234
00:12:01,350 --> 00:12:03,150
What tunnel, for God's sake?

235
00:12:03,950 --> 00:12:06,850
I asked her that too, she said curious children lose their ears.

236
00:12:10,520 --> 00:12:10,960
Right.

237
00:12:12,550 --> 00:12:13,850
Cocoa gives me hives.

238
00:12:14,380 --> 00:12:15,280
Mom says, right?

239
00:12:15,380 --> 00:12:15,780
Yeah.

240
00:12:16,250 --> 00:12:17,050
Risk it.

241
00:12:58,450 --> 00:12:59,410
Good day.

242
00:12:59,590 --> 00:13:00,250
Praise be.

243
00:13:00,550 --> 00:13:01,290
Praise be.

244
00:13:01,850 --> 00:13:03,250
What are you playing?

245
00:13:03,650 --> 00:13:05,270
Christian band Lazari.

246
00:13:13,720 --> 00:13:21,410
Where did you get all this overnight?

247
00:13:21,490 --> 00:13:23,410
I found a company called God's Emergency Services.

248
00:13:23,410 --> 00:13:28,910
24 hours a day, except Sundays, Easter, Christmas, Pentecost, and the feast of Blessed Hroznata.

249
00:13:29,450 --> 00:13:32,650
But getting to the supplier list was a real Calvary.

250
00:13:38,050 --> 00:13:39,230
Where else would I put it?

251
00:13:39,410 --> 00:13:40,550
Where else would I put it?

252
00:13:42,990 --> 00:13:44,570
People, it's a blessing in here, right?

253
00:13:44,770 --> 00:13:46,070
Because Ozzak isn't here.

254
00:13:46,750 --> 00:13:50,450
Well, it's true he could scare them off a bit.

255
00:13:50,650 --> 00:13:54,750
I found this stuck to the door when I was opening up.

256
00:14:02,050 --> 00:14:04,450
Couldn't we just get by without him for a few days?

257
00:14:04,540 --> 00:14:06,520
Marcelka, his pranks are over.

258
00:14:06,660 --> 00:14:08,600
As soon as he wakes up, I'll put a stop to it.

259
00:14:08,700 --> 00:14:10,440
That's not possible, but I'm worried about Zoran.

260
00:14:10,720 --> 00:14:12,100
Did Ozzak do something to him too?

261
00:14:12,200 --> 00:14:14,680
No, but he could lose his audience because of him.

262
00:14:14,800 --> 00:14:17,700
What if the Pope found out he works with such a heathen?

263
00:14:18,100 --> 00:14:19,420
How would he find out?

264
00:14:19,600 --> 00:14:21,820
The Vatican is incredibly thorough.

265
00:14:21,820 --> 00:14:28,650
The mayor, for example, lost his audience just because his city has a district called Dablice.

266
00:14:40,930 --> 00:14:41,410
Ozzak!

267
00:14:45,120 --> 00:14:45,600
Simona?

268
00:14:46,200 --> 00:14:46,680
Tomas?

269
00:14:47,350 --> 00:14:48,450
What's going on here?

270
00:14:49,250 --> 00:14:50,750
You tell me.

271
00:14:51,250 --> 00:14:57,950
Well, I come home, the door's wide open, one chair is in the hallway and you're holding the other one.

272
00:14:58,550 --> 00:14:59,250
Right. That's...

273
00:15:01,350 --> 00:15:03,350
Unbelievable, what's happening today.

274
00:15:05,550 --> 00:15:06,380
Wait, where are you going?

275
00:15:06,750 --> 00:15:07,550
I have to run.

276
00:15:08,140 --> 00:15:08,620
Wait!

277
00:15:09,350 --> 00:15:10,550
You're not going to tell me anything?

278
00:15:10,550 --> 00:15:10,930
Sorry.

279
00:15:10,950 --> 00:15:11,490
Bye.

280
00:15:20,450 --> 00:15:25,920
The mayor's proposal to rename Zizkov to the Saint Ignatius district will be discussed by the council today.

281
00:15:25,920 --> 00:15:26,560
What?

282
00:15:26,720 --> 00:15:28,220
Why didn't they wake me? Is it noon?

283
00:15:29,050 --> 00:15:30,850
You've got the day off, you scare the faithful.

284
00:15:31,250 --> 00:15:32,650
Were you out with Ziza last night?

285
00:15:33,550 --> 00:15:34,250
No, why?

286
00:15:34,850 --> 00:15:35,850
Nothing, nothing.

287
00:15:36,350 --> 00:15:37,650
Ozzak, what did you do?

288
00:15:38,240 --> 00:15:38,880
Nothing.

289
00:15:40,250 --> 00:15:42,250
It was such a blast last night at Satan.

290
00:15:42,450 --> 00:15:43,850
What blast?

291
00:15:44,150 --> 00:15:51,900
We were just having a beer and suddenly some guy in a red skirt shows up and starts freaking out that the Pope is coming through tomorrow and the pub has to be shut down.

292
00:15:51,900 --> 00:15:53,260
And that it's a scandal.

293
00:15:54,650 --> 00:15:56,440
A guy in a red skirt?

294
00:15:56,650 --> 00:15:57,650
Yeah, a weirdo.

295
00:15:58,350 --> 00:16:01,350
Ziza got a bit wound up and swiped his radio.

296
00:16:05,850 --> 00:16:06,680
Ozzak.

297
00:16:06,680 --> 00:16:07,200
What?

298
00:16:07,280 --> 00:16:08,060
He started it.

299
00:16:08,750 --> 00:16:12,420
Don't you understand that some believers might have a problem with Satan?

300
00:16:12,420 --> 00:16:14,080
What do believers have to do with a pub?

301
00:16:14,320 --> 00:16:15,560
Jesus, what pub?

302
00:16:15,740 --> 00:16:16,660
The guy was a wreck.

303
00:16:17,350 --> 00:16:20,850
He said if they close Kremenace in Liberec too, he's completely done for.

304
00:16:32,220 --> 00:16:32,820
Hey.

305
00:16:34,050 --> 00:16:35,250
Hi, Ivuska.

306
00:16:41,450 --> 00:16:42,850
Why are there cranberries in my room?

307
00:16:43,850 --> 00:16:45,350
I've started clearing out.

308
00:16:46,150 --> 00:16:47,750
We can't save the basement.

309
00:16:47,780 --> 00:16:48,380
Really?

310
00:16:49,650 --> 00:16:50,850
I visited everyone.

311
00:16:51,350 --> 00:16:58,800
Pajerova made me sort through a trash can as a demonstration and then said she still can't vote for someone who doesn't know what biomass is.

312
00:16:58,800 --> 00:16:59,400
Damn.

313
00:17:00,140 --> 00:17:01,500
She's super green.

314
00:17:01,500 --> 00:17:06,480
At Podrouzek's place there were cops and they said he won't be attending meetings for three to five years.

315
00:17:06,950 --> 00:17:13,250
And Vojtickova said she'd vote for us, but only if Ozzak repented.

316
00:17:16,350 --> 00:17:17,450
Which is nonsense.

317
00:17:18,260 --> 00:17:19,120
Did you see that?

318
00:17:19,120 --> 00:17:20,950
That's the ultimate holy frisbee.

319
00:17:22,150 --> 00:17:25,430
I begged you on my knees to hide that somewhere.

320
00:17:25,430 --> 00:17:26,150
What are you on about?

321
00:17:26,650 --> 00:17:30,150
Tonight at Satan's we'll have a great tournament.

322
00:17:31,250 --> 00:17:32,550
What was that hat?

323
00:17:33,550 --> 00:17:34,850
Please don't ask.

324
00:17:34,850 --> 00:17:37,180
Dad, it'll be fine.

325
00:17:37,180 --> 00:17:37,660
Fine?

326
00:17:38,350 --> 00:17:40,050
How can it be fine?

327
00:17:40,880 --> 00:17:42,300
The building manager is clearly coming after us.

328
00:17:42,760 --> 00:17:44,520
Everyone in the building hates us.

329
00:17:44,600 --> 00:17:48,800
And once Vojtickova finds out who that hat belongs to, she'll really sound the attack.

330
00:17:49,550 --> 00:17:53,320
Can't Ziza just ring the doorbell?

331
00:17:53,320 --> 00:17:54,840
Like a normal person?

332
00:17:55,380 --> 00:17:56,360
Bro, she's not stupid.

333
00:17:56,500 --> 00:17:58,200
You know I switched the names on the doorbells?

334
00:17:59,640 --> 00:18:14,610
What's going on, Marcelka?

335
00:18:14,630 --> 00:18:15,410
You called for me.

336
00:18:16,850 --> 00:18:18,350
I caught the thief.

337
00:18:20,300 --> 00:18:20,780
Simona?

338
00:18:21,040 --> 00:18:21,420
That's enough.

339
00:18:21,820 --> 00:18:23,920
I was starting to think I'd have to call the police.

340
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:26,540
Excuse me, the police should be called on you.

341
00:18:26,640 --> 00:18:27,540
Oh yeah, and for what?

342
00:18:28,050 --> 00:18:29,750
You think I'm completely stupid?

343
00:18:29,880 --> 00:18:33,260
She comes in saying she urgently needs a list of Johann Strauss Jr.'s operettas.

344
00:18:33,320 --> 00:18:36,060
And when I come back from the storeroom with the catalogue, the armchairs are gone.

345
00:18:37,920 --> 00:18:38,360
Armchairs.

346
00:18:39,100 --> 00:18:40,220
What nonsense, right?

347
00:18:40,700 --> 00:18:41,620
It had to be her.

348
00:18:41,740 --> 00:18:43,580
The only other people in the shop were nuns.

349
00:18:44,450 --> 00:18:46,950
Great, and she's blaming it on me.

350
00:18:46,960 --> 00:18:48,840
Simona, this is really a bit weird, okay?

351
00:18:49,100 --> 00:18:51,340
First the chairs, now the armchairs.

352
00:18:51,460 --> 00:18:54,680
Well, you've really outdone yourself, you should be proud.

353
00:18:54,740 --> 00:18:54,840
What?

354
00:18:55,360 --> 00:18:59,720
Accusing an unemployed mother of two small children of stealing your smelly armchairs?

355
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:01,460
Wait, nobody's saying that.

356
00:19:01,680 --> 00:19:02,400
I'm saying it.

357
00:19:02,760 --> 00:19:03,760
Fine, we'll clear it up.

358
00:19:04,360 --> 00:19:09,160
Simona, if you were here when the armchairs disappeared, you must have seen something.

359
00:19:10,350 --> 00:19:12,850
Well, of course I did.

360
00:19:14,050 --> 00:19:16,750
I saw Ozzak carrying them into the storeroom.

361
00:19:18,650 --> 00:19:19,550
Ozzak was at home.

362
00:19:20,250 --> 00:19:21,450
And I was in the storeroom.

363
00:19:22,050 --> 00:19:23,150
Damn.

364
00:19:23,650 --> 00:19:24,910
That's quite a mystery.

365
00:19:25,450 --> 00:19:26,730
I really don't envy you.

366
00:19:27,150 --> 00:19:27,770
Well, I'm off.

367
00:19:27,770 --> 00:19:30,350
Simona, I'm not letting you go anywhere until this is cleared up.

368
00:19:30,350 --> 00:19:31,090
Sure, we'll clear it up.

369
00:19:31,190 --> 00:19:32,310
Let's do a reconstruction.

370
00:19:32,450 --> 00:19:33,330
I'll go to the storeroom.

371
00:19:34,230 --> 00:19:34,790
Wait.

372
00:19:35,570 --> 00:19:37,660
But I was the one in the storeroom.

373
00:19:46,550 --> 00:19:47,650
Marcelka?

374
00:19:48,050 --> 00:19:48,650
Yes?

375
00:19:50,250 --> 00:19:51,550
Get off me.

376
00:19:58,950 --> 00:19:59,800
Ivo, we're saved.

377
00:20:00,050 --> 00:20:00,850
What's going on?

378
00:20:01,830 --> 00:20:02,530
Simona steals.

379
00:20:02,810 --> 00:20:03,210
What?

380
00:20:03,530 --> 00:20:07,170
When people find out Simona's been stealing around the building, they'll go after her and leave us alone.

381
00:20:07,250 --> 00:20:08,350
What are you talking about?

382
00:20:08,990 --> 00:20:13,490
She stole the armchairs from the shop, so she also stole the ficus from the landing.

383
00:20:13,690 --> 00:20:15,390
Dad, calm down, why would she steal armchairs?

384
00:20:15,390 --> 00:20:17,210
To pay for drugs, otherwise it doesn't make sense.

385
00:20:17,250 --> 00:20:18,090
That's crazy.

386
00:20:18,650 --> 00:20:20,500
You want to rat out your friend?

387
00:20:20,500 --> 00:20:21,420
She stole armchairs.

388
00:20:21,540 --> 00:20:22,820
Why would she steal armchairs?

389
00:20:22,940 --> 00:20:23,980
To pay for drugs.

390
00:20:24,020 --> 00:20:24,840
And why would she do drugs?

391
00:20:24,980 --> 00:20:26,100
So it would make sense.

392
00:20:26,340 --> 00:20:27,820
Dad, please, calm down.

393
00:20:28,400 --> 00:20:29,220
At night...

394
00:20:31,750 --> 00:20:35,250
They don't sell drugs in the tunnel, and for the armchairs she wouldn't even get a straw.

395
00:20:35,250 --> 00:20:37,250
Wait, I'm talking about drugs you snort.

396
00:20:37,650 --> 00:20:38,850
Nobody's snorting anything.

397
00:20:40,350 --> 00:20:41,750
I have no idea what you're talking about now.

398
00:20:42,350 --> 00:20:43,450
And honestly, I'm glad.

399
00:20:44,650 --> 00:20:46,150
Won't you all come with me?

400
00:20:46,390 --> 00:20:47,270
They closed Satan!

401
00:20:50,550 --> 00:20:55,020
I repeat, nobody is going to protest for some pub.

402
00:20:55,020 --> 00:20:57,160
If I see anyone with banners, they're moving out.

403
00:20:57,280 --> 00:20:59,000
So we're just supposed to take this, bro?

404
00:20:59,410 --> 00:21:02,550
Because of some Pope they shut down the last good pub in Prague.

405
00:21:02,690 --> 00:21:03,830
How do you know it's because of the Pope?

406
00:21:03,990 --> 00:21:06,030
Some weirdo in a red skirt showed up there yesterday.

407
00:21:06,110 --> 00:21:07,170
Cardinal Bursik.

408
00:21:07,330 --> 00:21:09,210
And today the health inspectors show up, coincidence?

409
00:21:09,750 --> 00:21:12,970
Bro, even the biggest idiot can put two and two together.

410
00:21:15,150 --> 00:21:15,850
Let's go.

411
00:21:15,910 --> 00:21:16,430
Nowhere.

412
00:21:18,650 --> 00:21:21,850
And you still dare to show your face after all that.

413
00:21:21,930 --> 00:21:22,450
Oh.

414
00:21:23,350 --> 00:21:25,950
And I thought you'd like to see your armchairs.

415
00:21:26,180 --> 00:21:26,700
Where?

416
00:21:32,850 --> 00:21:33,950
I smell beer.

417
00:21:35,350 --> 00:21:41,650
Simona, I swear, if you yell "watch out, monitor lizard" now, we are done for good, got it?

418
00:21:57,350 --> 00:21:58,390
You're stunned, huh?

419
00:21:58,850 --> 00:21:59,650
What is this?

420
00:22:00,250 --> 00:22:03,750
A pub! Satan Around the Corner, bro!

421
00:22:07,150 --> 00:22:07,770
A pub?

422
00:22:08,010 --> 00:22:09,230
This is a bunker?

423
00:22:10,150 --> 00:22:12,200
Well, if there's a war, we're screwed.

424
00:22:12,750 --> 00:22:15,950
But until then, Horvath's brother at the ministry will cover it up.

425
00:22:16,420 --> 00:22:17,060
Sure.

426
00:22:26,860 --> 00:22:28,480
There's going to be trouble.

427
00:22:28,820 --> 00:22:29,980
You've always been a coward.

428
00:22:30,610 --> 00:22:31,670
Excuse me?

429
00:22:31,990 --> 00:22:33,670
You are, that's why I didn't tell you.

430
00:22:34,050 --> 00:22:39,470
But the thing is, thanks to you Ozzak doesn't want to settle anything with the Pope anymore.

431
00:22:39,470 --> 00:22:40,550
Me? No way.

432
00:22:40,810 --> 00:22:42,070
One more and I'm going.

433
00:22:43,750 --> 00:22:47,250
And if not me, then Ziza will get revenge for all of us.

434
00:22:47,350 --> 00:22:53,430
How can you possibly think you can just open a pub without a permit?

435
00:22:53,850 --> 00:22:55,550
But with my armchairs.

436
00:22:55,650 --> 00:22:58,150
I'll return them once this gets going.

437
00:22:58,470 --> 00:22:59,050
Tomorrow!

438
00:23:00,950 --> 00:23:05,940
I actually applied for a permit, but they'd only give it to me if I had a cook-waiter qualification or a relative with one.

439
00:23:06,450 --> 00:23:08,150
And I've got asphalt worker-insulator.

440
00:23:11,550 --> 00:23:12,850
What am I actually drinking?

441
00:23:12,890 --> 00:23:13,470
Mojito.

442
00:23:14,050 --> 00:23:15,050
That's what you wanted.

443
00:23:17,450 --> 00:23:18,850
Where's the mint?

444
00:23:19,310 --> 00:23:19,890
Mint?

445
00:23:20,650 --> 00:23:22,150
Aren't you fancy.

446
00:23:22,450 --> 00:23:23,950
There's green, beer and ficus.

447
00:23:27,050 --> 00:23:29,150
Just like from Fidel.

448
00:23:30,530 --> 00:23:31,110
Fidl.

449
00:23:32,950 --> 00:23:34,050
The building manager.

450
00:24:01,150 --> 00:24:04,090
And now we see the mayor walking alongside the popemobile.

451
00:24:04,090 --> 00:24:06,510
He's flagellating himself and gazing meaningfully at the Holy Father.

452
00:24:06,850 --> 00:24:08,950
The Pope, however, is looking the other way.

453
00:24:09,150 --> 00:24:12,960
Still, if Mr. Ozzak had tackled the Pope, we'd be learning about him in school.

454
00:24:13,150 --> 00:24:17,350
I don't know where they were, but they came back with Dad so wasted they couldn't even tip over a trash can.

455
00:24:19,050 --> 00:24:20,250
How is this going to end?

456
00:24:20,730 --> 00:24:25,190
If the building manager sees them in this state, we'll lose not only the basement but also the keys to the attic.

457
00:24:25,270 --> 00:24:27,490
And I'll be stuck with cranberries in my room for the rest of my life.

458
00:24:27,790 --> 00:24:29,030
You have cranberries?

459
00:24:29,450 --> 00:24:30,350
A whole room full.

460
00:24:30,850 --> 00:24:32,290
Lucky you.

461
00:24:32,750 --> 00:24:34,350
I'm never getting married.

462
00:24:39,350 --> 00:24:41,450
Fellow club member!

463
00:24:52,450 --> 00:24:53,350
Ivuska?

464
00:24:53,850 --> 00:24:57,550
Don't you want to ask me something?

465
00:24:58,250 --> 00:24:59,750
Why are you sitting next to the couch?

466
00:25:00,050 --> 00:25:14,550
But you don't want to ask me anything else.

467
00:25:15,350 --> 00:25:16,450
How did the meeting go?

468
00:25:17,150 --> 00:25:19,550
Right question.

469
00:25:24,750 --> 00:25:26,950
It couldn't have gone better.

470
00:25:26,960 --> 00:25:27,620
Really?

471
00:25:27,620 --> 00:25:29,400
What did the building manager say?

472
00:25:29,400 --> 00:25:30,100
Nothing.

473
00:25:31,750 --> 00:25:34,150
She didn't even show up, sweetheart.

474
00:25:35,250 --> 00:25:38,130
For the first time in the history of the meetings.

475
00:25:38,750 --> 00:25:39,650
Is that possible?

476
00:25:40,150 --> 00:25:41,650
Nobody knows.

477
00:25:42,550 --> 00:25:59,180
But it might have something to do with the fact that two hooligans piled so many trash cans in front of her door that she couldn't get out of her apartment at all.

478
00:26:01,150 --> 00:26:01,850
Poor thing, nobody heard her.

479
00:26:02,550 --> 00:26:07,080
Just two hooligans?

480
00:26:07,550 --> 00:26:10,450
But they weren't hooligans.

481
00:26:10,550 --> 00:26:12,770
They saved the basement, didn't they?

482
00:26:13,450 --> 00:26:16,350
They were heroes.

483
00:26:32,180 --> 00:26:33,520
Good evening.

484
00:26:33,520 --> 00:26:38,620
I'm very sorry to bother you at such an ungodly hour, but...

485
00:26:38,620 --> 00:26:39,040
That's alright.

486
00:26:39,160 --> 00:26:39,820
Thank you.

487
00:26:40,650 --> 00:26:45,050
It's about Jarmila, the building manager.

488
00:26:45,750 --> 00:26:48,740
Someone barricaded her in her apartment.

489
00:26:49,550 --> 00:26:53,210
I can't lift those trash cans.

490
00:26:53,250 --> 00:26:57,570
I've already been to every apartment, but nobody opened.

491
00:26:57,570 --> 00:26:58,050
Sure.

492
00:26:58,050 --> 00:27:01,890
Dad's probably not here, but my uncle will definitely help you.

493
00:27:01,890 --> 00:27:02,630
Of course.

494
00:27:03,150 --> 00:27:05,050
And I've been at the trash cans.

495
00:27:05,710 --> 00:27:08,650
Actually, I'd rather not bother you.

496
00:27:08,810 --> 00:27:11,250
We'll manage with Jarmilka somehow.

497
00:27:11,310 --> 00:27:13,170
Don't be silly, you can't haul those by yourself.

498
00:27:13,290 --> 00:27:14,250
He'll be glad to help.

499
00:27:17,750 --> 00:27:22,600
He's the one who needs the most help, Ivuska.

500
00:27:23,850 --> 00:27:25,550
You see, his heart...

501
00:27:25,850 --> 00:27:27,950
...has been taken over by Satan.

502
00:27:28,150 --> 00:27:29,250
It was acting up.

503
00:27:29,850 --> 00:27:31,250
Apparently Satan is finished.

504
00:27:32,780 --> 00:27:33,460
It's...

505
00:27:34,650 --> 00:27:36,950
Hosanna.

506
00:27:44,760 --> 00:27:45,440
The pub.

507
00:27:46,000 --> 00:27:47,200
We'll all help you.

508
00:27:47,240 --> 00:27:47,580
Let's go.

509
00:27:48,080 --> 00:28:09,330
From here I can't quite tell what's happening.

510
00:28:09,330 --> 00:28:12,070
It looks as if the popemobile's path has been blocked by some kind of...

511
00:28:12,550 --> 00:28:17,150
Well, it appears to be a sewage truck with a chalice painted on the side.

512
00:28:18,850 --> 00:28:20,450
That's Ziza.
